{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"lookupCertificateIssuer","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"TLSCertificateT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"certificate"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TLSCertificateT"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"interaction","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"TLSInteractionRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO17TLSInteractionRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSInteractionRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"flags"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GTlsDatabaseLookupFlags","preciseIdentifier":"c:@EA@GTlsDatabaseLookupFlags","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef"},{"text":"? = nil) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificateRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO17TLSCertificateRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TLSCertificateRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"! "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TLSCertificateT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificateProtocol","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TLSCertificateProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO22TLSCertificateProtocolP"}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function can block. Use "},{"code":"g_tls_database_lookup_certificate_issuer_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to perform the lookup operation asynchronously."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Beware this function cannot be used to build certification paths. The","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"issuer certificate returned by this function may not be the same as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the certificate that would actually be used to construct a valid","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"certification path during certificate verification.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/datatracker.ietf.org\/doc\/html\/rfc4158","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" explains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"why an issuer certificate cannot be naively assumed to be part of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the certification path (though GLib’s TLS backends may not follow the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"path building strategies outlined in this RFC). Due to the complexity"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of certification path building, GLib does not provide any way to know"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"which certification path will actually be used when verifying a TLS"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"certificate. Accordingly, this function cannot be used to make","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"security-related decisions. Only GLib itself should make security"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"decisions about TLS certificates.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"extendedModule":"GIO","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"lookupCertificateIssuer","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text